research_municipality_step.notes: Alamo Heights, TX operates under a Council-Manager form of government. The City Council consists of an elected Mayor and five Council Members, all chosen at large. Al Honigblum became Mayor after running unopposed in the May 2025 election. Trey Jacobson was appointed to Place 5 in August 2024 to replace John Savage and is running for the remainder of the term, with the seat up for re-election in 2026.
